  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNIDO#s strengthened global advocacy: Promoting inclusive and sustainable industrial development through improved communication mechanisms</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to strengthen UNIDO&#x2019;s global advocacy in promoting inclusive and sustainable industrial development through improved communication mechanisms.
While the Organization has successfully delivered various promotional campaigns and communication plans over the years&#x2013; these efforts should be further enhanced, focusing not only on individual projects and programme activities, but also by increasing efforts on effective global advocacy and communication.
Hence, a new structure for the Advocacy and Media Relations Division and a shared service model based on ROTC are proposed to warrant successful communications deliverables for technical and non-technical operations, while allowing for an amplification of UNIDO&#x2019;s advocacy and visibility in the global development context. Furthermore, the development and distribution of a Communications Kit, consisting of a new UNIDO Corporate Identity Manual to enable for a modern and innovative but also a coherent and consistent presentation of UNIDO, and a UNIDO Communications Booklet, which explains in detail how to better use communication products and allows for providing the same messages to transmit coherence and credibility, will be pursued.
A core team of EPR/ETR/AMR, comprising of the following units shall achieve the above-mentioned objective:

1.Advisory Service Unit, shall provide guidance, assessment and quality assurance to UNIDO&#x2019;s PTC and non-PTC Departments/Divisions requests for support, in collaboration with the Communications Officer of PTC and other communication focal points;

2.Content Creation Unit, shall be responsible for researching, drafting and editing texts and developing visuals for publication and using multimedia tools to promote activities and events as well as their impact and outcomes;

3.Strategic Advocacy Unit, shall develop the communications strategy and the annual communications plan for UNIDO, and focus on global initiatives of the Organization (4IR, PCP, IDDA 3), the integration of technical success stories into global advocacy efforts and the Organization&#x2019;s engagement in UN-driven campaigns (UN75 and Decade of Action, EXPO2020, etc.).

All three units will be responsible for supporting the installation of the necessary mechanisms, including the development of compulsory principles and guidelines set through an Administrative Issuance.</narrative>
  </description>
